  "prompt": "What are some good movies about a person that has a hidden power that he/she couldn't use until put into a pressure situation?",
  "response": "This is a great movie trope! Here are some good examples, categorized a bit for clarity:\n\n**Superhero Adjacent:**\n\n*   **Unbreakable (2000):** M. Night Shyamalan's deconstruction of superhero origins. David Dunn discovers he's nearly invulnerable after surviving a train crash, but it takes increasingly dangerous situations to awaken his abilities. The pressure to protect others triggers his powers.\n\n*   **Hancock (2008):** While Hancock knows he has powers, he doesn't fully understand their extent or how to control them until he encounters Mary.  His connection to her, and the circumstances surrounding her own powers, are the pressure cooker that forces him to confront his limitations.\n\n*   **Chronicle (2012):**  Three high school friends gain telekinetic powers, but the psychological pressure of their own lives and the temptations of their abilities drive them to different outcomes.  Andrew, the bullied and abused protagonist, is pushed to his breaking point, unlocking the full, devastating potential of his powers.\n\n*   **Brightburn (2019):** This is a dark and twisted take on the Superman story. A boy with extraordinary powers struggles to control them and eventually gives in to a dark and destructive path when under pressure from his own internal conflicts and societal pressures.\n\n**Action/Thriller/Sci-Fi:**\n\n*   **Limitless (2011):** While not exactly a *hidden* power, Eddie Morra only unlocks his full intellectual potential through NZT-48.  The pressure of living a successful life, avoiding dangerous enemies, and maintaining his access to the drug pushes him to exploit its benefits and develop strategies beyond anyone's expectations.\n\n*   **Lucy (2014):**  Scarlett Johansson's character gains access to 100% of her brain capacity after a drug accident.  The pressure of being hunted by gangsters, and the desire to understand her rapidly evolving abilities, forces her to accelerate her evolution.\n\n*   **Push (2009):** A group of people with different psychic powers are hunted by a shadowy organization. The pressure of survival forces them to use their abilities in creative and unexpected ways, discovering new aspects of their powers in the process.\n\n*   **Jumper (2008):** David Rice discovers he can teleport (jump) when under stress. The pressure of being hunted by Paladins (who hunt Jumpers) forces him to master his abilities and confront his past.\n\n**Horror/Supernatural:**\n\n*   **Carrie (1976 / 2013):**  Carrie White is a shy, bullied teenager who discovers she has telekinetic powers, which she unleashes in a devastating display of rage after being humiliated at her prom. The extreme pressure and public humiliation unlock her full, destructive potential.\n\n*   **Firestarter (1984 / 2022):**  Charlie McGee, the daughter of two participants in a government experiment that gave them psychic abilities, has pyrokinetic powers.  The pressure of being hunted by the Shop and protecting her father pushes her to develop and control her abilities.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Character Development:**  The best movies in this genre focus on the character's internal struggle with their powers and the moral implications of using them.\n\n*   **The Source of the Pressure:**  The pressure can come from external forces (enemies, government agencies) or internal struggles (fear, self-doubt, repressed emotions).\n\n*   **The Nature of the Power:**  The specific nature of the power (telepathy, telekinesis, precognition, etc.) influences the types of situations that trigger it and the ways the character can use it.\n\nWhen choosing a movie from this list, consider what subgenre you prefer (action, horror, superhero) and whether you want a more character-driven story or a more action-packed one.  Enjoy!\n",
